narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This course was very insightful because I began this class with no knowledge on the modern business world; However, after taking this class, I have a decent grasp on how the film companies function and the market their films.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The course is a lecture for an hour 45 minutes which a little bit too long to stay locked in. Some discussion time would be welcomed. Additionally, taking exams prior to class is a stretch on the time demanded on the student.

Sometimes the course get a little dull which made it hard to focus and pay attention in class. The instructions given can be blurry sometimes because I had trouble finding what are the assignments and where I submit them because normally teacher would just create an assignment and require the students to submit on the same place as the assignment module.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: No, unless you're interested in working in this industry.
I would becasue as I said, it was super insightful on the topic and expanded my knowledge in the field. The reading was very helpful, direct, and related which advanced my learning skills.

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.
How will you use the knowledge and skills you learned in this course in your future endeavors?
comments: This course helped me create more detailed examples for future business courses to apply concepts to.
